\N<Luda Soldier>The people of this town are lucky. There are places that
have been massacred without question. Be thankful to Lord
Zuuteruka.

\N<Woman>It's widely rumored that not a single plant remains where
the people of Luda have passed...

\N<Woman>Of course, it's probably a rumor that's been exaggerated,
but even so, I worry about the future of this town...

\N<Man>That management office used to be quite literally the nerve

\N<Man>Well... now it's completely turned into the administrative
governing body for the Luda troops stationed in this

\N<Man>The management office over there used to be quite literally

\N<Man>The management office over there used to be quite literally

\N<Man>Well... now it's completely turned into the administrative

\N<Luda Soldier>Inside, you'll find the town's garrison commander, Lord
Zuuteruka. Be very careful about how you speak.

\N<Luda Soldier>Access beyond this point is prohibited due to an
investigation of the remnants of the deserters.

\N<Segi>...Mr. Rozaro. Did you need something at the management
office?

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it's about the next battle. But the fact that you're
here means...
\N<Segi>Yes... it turns out you are my next opponent, Mr. Rozaro.

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it seems so. Miss Segi, your efforts up to this point
are commendable. I might even say more than I expected.

\N<Rozaro>But this is literally a fight for our lives. Naturally, I
can't afford to lose either. At the very least... let's face
each other fair and square.

\N<Rozaro>I'll go with you, I felt bad about it but I've listened to
the story. Above all, I'm worried about Riia's safety, and I
myself have a deep grudge against that Zeda guy.

\N<Rozaro>Moreover, I've heard that the lowest level of the ruins is
riddled with countless traps, it's dangerous for you to go
alone.

\N<Rozaro>I understand how you feel. However, now is not the time to
be swayed by personal feelings.

\N<Rozaro>Riia is in imminent danger, now more than ever we should
help each other, right?
\N<Rozaro>Hmm... Now that it's decided, let's hurry.
\N<Segi>Is there really no effective way to save Riia...?

\N<Segi>Is that really true? If, as Zuuteruka says, the main forces
of Luda desire something so much, then surely the answer
must lie beyond that door...?

\N<Segi>The keyhole bore a striking resemblance to Lord Yuia's
necklace... If that's the case, Lord Yuia must know
something...
\N<Segi>...Wait. Is that why Lord Yuia is being kept alive...?

\N<Segi>It's true that it was the result of my pleading, but is that
all there is to it...?

\N<Segi>Princess Consort and Mother... If the two of you are still
alive, why is that?

\N<Segi>As mere mistresses to the men of Luda? There are countless
other women who are just as beautiful...
\N<Segi>And above all, why am I... why am I being kept alive?
\N<Segi>Why are those related to Lord Yuia... being kept alive?

\N<Segi>But even if Lord Yuia knows something... if Zuuteruka has
come to a similar conclusion, he must be wary of the content
of my conversations with Lord Yuia...
\N<Segi>I don't understand... what should I do...
